{
  "video_id": "eYS3-ShEnbs",
  "title": "Crash Course Big History #8: The Modern Revolution",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 60.0,
      "end_time": 1210.0,
      "text": "Hi, I&#39;m John Green."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 1210.0,
      "end_time": 2780.0,
      "text": "Welcome to Crash Course Big History."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 2780.0,
      "end_time": 5870.0,
      "text": "Today we&#39;re going to look at the modern revolution."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 5870.0,
      "end_time": 7060.0,
      "text": "Mr. Green, Mr. Green!"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 7060.0,
      "end_time": 8330.0,
      "text": "But what does modern even mean?"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 8330.0,
      "end_time": 10060.0,
      "text": "I mean, I know that fax machines"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 10060.0,
      "end_time": 12720.0,
      "text": "and Super Nintendo are modern, but, like, people used to think"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 12720.0,
      "end_time": 14870.0,
      "text": "that toilets that flushed were modern."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 14870.0,
      "end_time": 16420.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s actually a pretty perceptive question,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 16420.0,
      "end_time": 17600.0,
      "text": "me from the past."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 17600.0,
      "end_time": 19000.0,
      "text": "So, if we&#39;re going to talk about modernity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 19000.0,
      "end_time": 20780.0,
      "text": "we should probably define modernity."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 20780.0,
      "end_time": 22660.0,
      "text": "But first, I have great news."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 22660.0,
      "end_time": 24150.0,
      "text": "There is a future me from the past"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 24150.0,
      "end_time": 28510.0,
      "text": "where video games are so much better than Super Nintendo."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 28510.0,
      "end_time": 33150.0,
      "text": "In fact, this machine plays 24,000 games"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 33150.0,
      "end_time": 35780.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;s in the office of future you."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 35780.0,
      "end_time": 36810.0,
      "text": "What were we talking about?"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 36810.0,
      "end_time": 38360.0,
      "text": "Oh, right, modernity."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 38360.0,
      "end_time": 40570.0,
      "text": "So, some historians date the beginning of the modern era"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 40570.0,
      "end_time": 42750.0,
      "text": "with the beginnings of the Industrial Revolution"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 42750.0,
      "end_time": 44060.0,
      "text": "in the 19th century."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 44060.0,
      "end_time": 46180.0,
      "text": "Some date it to the French Revolution in 1789."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 46180.0,
      "end_time": 47420.0,
      "text": "Some push it further back"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 47420.0,
      "end_time": 50240.0,
      "text": "to 16th and 17th century European colonialism."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 50240.0,
      "end_time": 52840.0,
      "text": "And some date modernity with the European Renaissance"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 52840.0,
      "end_time": 56540.0,
      "text": "and call anything past the year 1500 &quot;early modern.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 56540.0,
      "end_time": 59420.0,
      "text": "But through aBig Historylens, all of these are just signs"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 59420.0,
      "end_time": 61870.0,
      "text": "of acceleration in human collective learning,"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 61870.0,
      "end_time": 65030.0,
      "text": "which was already underway and took its first tiny steps"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 65030.0,
      "end_time": 67840.0,
      "text": "in East Africa 250,000 years ago."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 67840.0,
      "end_time": 69480.0,
      "text": "Then again, it would be silly"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 69480.0,
      "end_time": 72480.0,
      "text": "to call the first human foragers &quot;early-early-early modern.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 72480.0,
      "end_time": 79510.0,
      "text": "So for the purposes of today, let&#39;s say:"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 79510.0,
      "end_time": 82090.0,
      "text": "With an acknowledgment that it&#39;s all a little bit arbitrary."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 82090.0,
      "end_time": 83360.0,
      "text": "And I know what you&#39;re wondering,"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 83360.0,
      "end_time": 85330.0,
      "text": "but no, 1750 was several decades"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 85330.0,
      "end_time": 96390.0,
      "text": "before the first flushing toilets."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 96390.0,
      "end_time": 98420.0,
      "text": "So last week, we looked at how collective learning--"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 98420.0,
      "end_time": 101000.0,
      "text": "which relies on population numbers and connectivity"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 101000.0,
      "end_time": 103270.0,
      "text": "to produce new ideas-- grew by leaps and bounds"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 103270.0,
      "end_time": 104810.0,
      "text": "with the introduction of agriculture."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 104810.0,
      "end_time": 106690.0,
      "text": "By the year 1400, the human population"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 106690.0,
      "end_time": 109450.0,
      "text": "had advanced magnificently, but the world was still divided"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 109450.0,
      "end_time": 113750.0,
      "text": "into four isolated world zones: the Americas, Australasia,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 113750.0,
      "end_time": 115840.0,
      "text": "the Pacific, and Afro-Eurasia."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 115840.0,
      "end_time": 117510.0,
      "text": "From aBig Historyperspective,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 117510.0,
      "end_time": 119690.0,
      "text": "what makes the European explorations worthy"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 119690.0,
      "end_time": 122480.0,
      "text": "of a place in an episode called &quot;Modern Revolution&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 122480.0,
      "end_time": 126210.0,
      "text": "is that they eventually united all four world zones"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 126210.0,
      "end_time": 133240.0,
      "text": "into a global system."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 133240.0,
      "end_time": 136600.0,
      "text": "But why did the Europeans feel so motivated to expand?"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 136600.0,
      "end_time": 138570.0,
      "text": "Well, a lot of reasons."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 138570.0,
      "end_time": 142270.0,
      "text": "One, Ottoman dominance of overland trade routes with Asia,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 142270.0,
      "end_time": 145750.0,
      "text": "particularly after the conquest of Constantinople in 1453,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 145750.0,
      "end_time": 149180.0,
      "text": "made Europeans seek alternative routes to the populace"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 149180.0,
      "end_time": 150840.0,
      "text": "and rich lands of the East."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 150840.0,
      "end_time": 153540.0,
      "text": "Two, European states were fairly small compared to some"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 153540.0,
      "end_time": 156240.0,
      "text": "of the vast empires of Asia and needed to compete"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 156240.0,
      "end_time": 159450.0,
      "text": "for more resources to fuel their almost-constant wars."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 159450.0,
      "end_time": 161330.0,
      "text": "And three, the fruits of exploration"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 161330.0,
      "end_time": 163090.0,
      "text": "undoubtedly had positive effects,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 163090.0,
      "end_time": 164630.0,
      "text": "whether it be the many advanced inventions"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 164630.0,
      "end_time": 166420.0,
      "text": "and consumer goods imported from China"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 166420.0,
      "end_time": 169150.0,
      "text": "or the spices of India and Indonesia,"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 169150.0,
      "end_time": 171210.0,
      "text": "or crops from the Americas."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 171210.0,
      "end_time": 173390.0,
      "text": "That last one should not be underestimated."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 173390.0,
      "end_time": 175330.0,
      "text": "Crops like the potato-- which earned the nickname"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 175330.0,
      "end_time": 177660.0,
      "text": "&quot;ready-made bread&quot; because it was easy to prepare--"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 177660.0,
      "end_time": 180570.0,
      "text": "combined with maize and squashes and tomatoes"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 180570.0,
      "end_time": 182870.0,
      "text": "and various yams allowed farms in Europe"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 182870.0,
      "end_time": 184210.0,
      "text": "to support more people."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 184210.0,
      "end_time": 185630.0,
      "text": "This was also good for Asia,"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 185630.0,
      "end_time": 188300.0,
      "text": "where those crops were introduced in the 17th century."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 188300.0,
      "end_time": 190780.0,
      "text": "And let us not forget about the vast amounts of silver"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 190780.0,
      "end_time": 193420.0,
      "text": "that the Spanish &quot;acquired&quot; from the Americas"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 193420.0,
      "end_time": 196030.0,
      "text": "or the many cotton, tobacco, and sugar farms"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 196030.0,
      "end_time": 197780.0,
      "text": "that Europeans bolstered their economies with."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 197780.0,
      "end_time": 199210.0,
      "text": "The unification of the world zones"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 199210.0,
      "end_time": 201270.0,
      "text": "also had many, many negative effects."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 201270.0,
      "end_time": 203840.0,
      "text": "For instance, it was terrible for people who worked"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 203840.0,
      "end_time": 206300.0,
      "text": "on those cotton and tobacco and sugar farms."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 206300.0,
      "end_time": 209090.0,
      "text": "Europeans increasingly relied on African slaves,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 209090.0,
      "end_time": 211390.0,
      "text": "the first of whom were granted to the Portuguese"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 211390.0,
      "end_time": 214840.0,
      "text": "by African rulers, and then, you know, several centuries"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 214840.0,
      "end_time": 217570.0,
      "text": "of horror ensued with an incomprehensible number"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 217570.0,
      "end_time": 220780.0,
      "text": "of African slaves dying in the appalling conditions"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 220780.0,
      "end_time": 222330.0,
      "text": "of the Atlantic crossing."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 222330.0,
      "end_time": 223720.0,
      "text": "Life was also pretty miserable"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 223720.0,
      "end_time": 225480.0,
      "text": "for the slaves that survived the journey"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 225480.0,
      "end_time": 227660.0,
      "text": "and generations of their descendents."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 227660.0,
      "end_time": 230270.0,
      "text": "Also, because Afro-Eurasia was a modestly connected"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 230270.0,
      "end_time": 232540.0,
      "text": "thriving cesspool of disease,"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 232540.0,
      "end_time": 234810.0,
      "text": "Europeans had developed many immunities."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 234810.0,
      "end_time": 237390.0,
      "text": "When they started arriving in the previously isolated Americas"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 237390.0,
      "end_time": 240540.0,
      "text": "in the late 1400s and 1500s, the indigenous inhabitants"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 240540.0,
      "end_time": 243060.0,
      "text": "had no immunity to those diseases."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 243060.0,
      "end_time": 244840.0,
      "text": "This resulted in one of the most horrific events"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 244840.0,
      "end_time": 246450.0,
      "text": "in human history."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 246450.0,
      "end_time": 250180.0,
      "text": "A cocktail of various European diseases, most notably smallpox,"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 250180.0,
      "end_time": 252690.0,
      "text": "killed off an estimated 50 million people"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 252690.0,
      "end_time": 255180.0,
      "text": "in the Americas in little over a century."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 255180.0,
      "end_time": 257210.0,
      "text": "A similar tragedy played itself out in Australia"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 257209.99999999997,
      "end_time": 259869.99999999997,
      "text": "when Europeans started arriving there in the 18th century."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 259870.0,
      "end_time": 261360.0,
      "text": "Now, along with all this horrific stuff,"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 261360.0,
      "end_time": 263720.0,
      "text": "the unification of the world zones was, nevertheless,"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 263720.0,
      "end_time": 265540.0,
      "text": "a good thing for collective learning,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 265540.0,
      "end_time": 273600.0,
      "text": "which would eventually prove our salvation in many ways."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 273600.0,
      "end_time": 277660.0,
      "text": "Which is why people can now look at this on their smart phone."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 277660.0,
      "end_time": 279750.0,
      "text": "Anyway, the unification of the world zones did not"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 279750.0,
      "end_time": 281840.0,
      "text": "in itself lead to a breakthrough"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 281840.0,
      "end_time": 284420.0,
      "text": "in the way humans harvested matter and energy."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 284420.0,
      "end_time": 286390.0,
      "text": "The last major shift happened with the arrival"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 286390.0,
      "end_time": 288360.0,
      "text": "of agriculture 10,000 years prior."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 288360.0,
      "end_time": 291330.0,
      "text": "The colonizing European societies of the 16th, 17th,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 291330.0,
      "end_time": 293690.0,
      "text": "and 18th centuries remained agrarian."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 293690.0,
      "end_time": 297150.0,
      "text": "But the explorations did allow for a network of exchange"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 297150.0,
      "end_time": 299840.0,
      "text": "that eventually did lead to a major breakthrough"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 299840.0,
      "end_time": 302750.0,
      "text": "in how humans harnessed more energy and produced more"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 302750.0,
      "end_time": 306480.0,
      "text": "and more cultural complexity:"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 306480.0,
      "end_time": 308660.0,
      "text": "The Industrial Revolution began in Great Britain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 308660.0,
      "end_time": 310720.0,
      "text": "as they&#39;ll be happy to tell you, in the 18th century."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 310720.0,
      "end_time": 313720.0,
      "text": "But it was a global revolution involving collective learning"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 313720.0,
      "end_time": 316000.0,
      "text": "shared across the global system."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 316000.0,
      "end_time": 318240.0,
      "text": "But a number of innovations that kickstarted industry"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 318240.0,
      "end_time": 320840.0,
      "text": "originated in Britain, like the more intensified use"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 320840.0,
      "end_time": 324030.0,
      "text": "of steam engines or the use of coke to refine metal."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 324030.0,
      "end_time": 325660.0,
      "text": "Not that Coke-- yeah, that coke."
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 325660.0,
      "end_time": 327420.0,
      "text": "Also, they invented many textile machines"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 327420.0,
      "end_time": 332000.0,
      "text": "and Britain had lots of coal and it was relatively easy to mine."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 332000.0,
      "end_time": 333180.0,
      "text": "Thank you, trees that died hundreds"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 333180.0,
      "end_time": 334450.0,
      "text": "of millions of years ago."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 334450.0,
      "end_time": 336510.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re going to turn you into industry."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 336510.0,
      "end_time": 337600.0,
      "text": "And smog."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 337600.0,
      "end_time": 339240.0,
      "text": "But all those British breakthroughs"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 339240.0,
      "end_time": 341870.0,
      "text": "wouldn&#39;t have been possible without a huge global network"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 341870.0,
      "end_time": 344300.0,
      "text": "of trade that supplied raw materials like cotton"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 344300.0,
      "end_time": 345750.0,
      "text": "and that opened new markets"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 345750.0,
      "end_time": 347570.0,
      "text": "where Britain could sell its goods."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 347570.0,
      "end_time": 349870.0,
      "text": "And it wouldn&#39;t have been possible to expand that network"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 349870.0,
      "end_time": 352780.0,
      "text": "of trade in the first place without gun powder"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 352780.0,
      "end_time": 355270.0,
      "text": "and the compass, which both came from China."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 355270.0,
      "end_time": 356720.0,
      "text": "The methods of porcelain manufacture"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 356720.0,
      "end_time": 358450.0,
      "text": "that were important to the Industrial Revolution"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 358450.0,
      "end_time": 361120.0,
      "text": "in Britain also came from China via Germany."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 361120.0,
      "end_time": 362570.0,
      "text": "And the improved methods of farming,"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 362570.0,
      "end_time": 364270.0,
      "text": "which freed up many British farm workers"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 364270.0,
      "end_time": 366720.0,
      "text": "for industrial wage labor in the cities came"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 366720.0,
      "end_time": 368450.0,
      "text": "from Flanders in the Netherlands."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 368450.0,
      "end_time": 371540.0,
      "text": "Early designs for steam engines came from 18th century France,"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 371540.0,
      "end_time": 374030.0,
      "text": "and much of the designs for these machines depended"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 374030.0,
      "end_time": 376540.0,
      "text": "on mathematics preserved and transmitted"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 376540.0,
      "end_time": 378570.0,
      "text": "by Islamic and Hindu civilizations."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 378570.0,
      "end_time": 380360.0,
      "text": "So up until the end of the 18th century,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 380360.0,
      "end_time": 383780.0,
      "text": "virtually all production in human history was propelled"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 383780.0,
      "end_time": 388360.0,
      "text": "by human or animal muscle power, or else by wind and water power."
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 388360.0,
      "end_time": 391360.0,
      "text": "But it turned out the coal and oil had stored energy"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 391360.0,
      "end_time": 393690.0,
      "text": "from the sun that had built up over hundreds"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 393690.0,
      "end_time": 395240.0,
      "text": "of millions of years."
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 395240.0,
      "end_time": 397750.0,
      "text": "And using those resources dramatically increased"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 397750.0,
      "end_time": 399600.0,
      "text": "the energy that humans could harness."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 399600.0,
      "end_time": 402150.0,
      "text": "Huge numbers of goods could be produced by factories"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 402150.0,
      "end_time": 404780.0,
      "text": "at relatively low prices which meant that over many decades,"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 404780.0,
      "end_time": 407570.0,
      "text": "goods that had previously been seen as luxuries"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 407570.0,
      "end_time": 410720.0,
      "text": "by common people were suddenly viewed as necessities."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 410720.0,
      "end_time": 413330.0,
      "text": "By the 1900s, most Europeans enjoyed a standard"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 413330.0,
      "end_time": 416240.0,
      "text": "of living higher than the kings of the Middle Ages."
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 416240.0,
      "end_time": 418870.0,
      "text": "Coal and oil also allowed mechanization of agriculture,"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 418870.0,
      "end_time": 420420.0,
      "text": "which raised the carrying capacity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 420420.0,
      "end_time": 422000.0,
      "text": "increasing the population."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 422000.0,
      "end_time": 424300.0,
      "text": "And new modes of connectivity beginning with the telegraph,"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 424300.0,
      "end_time": 425780.0,
      "text": "and then later, the telephone,"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 425780.0,
      "end_time": 428480.0,
      "text": "increasingly bound the human species together,"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 428480.0,
      "end_time": 431600.0,
      "text": "allowing for swift and rapid exchange of ideas."
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 431600.0,
      "end_time": 434540.0,
      "text": "For 250,000 years, if I wanted to tell someone"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 434540.0,
      "end_time": 437000.0,
      "text": "who lived 100 miles away from me something,"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 437000.0,
      "end_time": 439300.0,
      "text": "it took me days to do so."
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 439300.0,
      "end_time": 442750.0,
      "text": "For the last 100 years, it&#39;s taken me seconds."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 442750.0,
      "end_time": 444690.0,
      "text": "Because a slight tweak in modes of production"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 444690.0,
      "end_time": 446450.0,
      "text": "in the 18th century and the adoption"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 446450.0,
      "end_time": 448600.0,
      "text": "of fossil fuels lead to an explosion"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 448600.0,
      "end_time": 451870.0,
      "text": "of productivity and invention in the 1800s and 1900s,"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 451870.0,
      "end_time": 455240.0,
      "text": "people often compare the Industrial Revolution"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 455240.0,
      "end_time": 458780.0,
      "text": "to the Cambrian explosion about 540 million years ago."
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 458780.0,
      "end_time": 468330.0,
      "text": "Remember:"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 468330.0,
      "end_time": 470030.0,
      "text": "In the Cambrian explosion, that evolutionary change"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 470030.0,
      "end_time": 471660.0,
      "text": "was biological."
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 471660.0,
      "end_time": 474270.0,
      "text": "In the Industrial Revolution, that increased pace"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 474270.0,
      "end_time": 475570.0,
      "text": "of change was cultural."
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 475570.0,
      "end_time": 477000.0,
      "text": "Consider bike design."
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 477000.0,
      "end_time": 480090.0,
      "text": "In the 1800s, there were many, many different designs"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 480090.0,
      "end_time": 484090.0,
      "text": "for bikes, some of which look amazingly, terrifyingly unsafe."
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 484090.0,
      "end_time": 485840.0,
      "text": "In the beginning of innovations for bicycles,"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 485840.0,
      "end_time": 489150.0,
      "text": "a huge number of designs filled all of the available niches."
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 489150.0,
      "end_time": 491330.0,
      "text": "Eventually, those designs started competing"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 491330.0,
      "end_time": 493870.0,
      "text": "with each other and a few forms won out."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 493870.0,
      "end_time": 496690.0,
      "text": "You&#39;ve got the road bike and the mountain bike and the BMX bike."
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 496690.0,
      "end_time": 499810.0,
      "text": "Just a little bit different variations of the same thing."
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 499810.0,
      "end_time": 502720.0,
      "text": "Another example is the adaptive radiation of electronics."
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 502720.0,
      "end_time": 505360.0,
      "text": "Take a look at all the stuff you needed in the 1980s"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 505360.0,
      "end_time": 508090.0,
      "text": "to do what your average cell phone can do today."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 508090.0,
      "end_time": 509870.0,
      "text": "And that was only a few decades ago."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 509870.0,
      "end_time": 512750.0,
      "text": "Many new ideas sparked an increase in the human standard"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 512750.0,
      "end_time": 515030.0,
      "text": "of living and the complexity of societies"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 515030.0,
      "end_time": 516390.0,
      "text": "in tons of different ways."
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 516390.0,
      "end_time": 518210.0,
      "text": "The explosion of cultural evolution"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 518210.00000000006,
      "end_time": 520660.00000000006,
      "text": "that started 200 years ago has yet to cease."
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 520659.99999999994,
      "end_time": 523149.99999999994,
      "text": "The Cambrian explosion went on for millions of years."
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 523150.0,
      "end_time": 525150.0,
      "text": "The Agricultural Revolution proceeded"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 525150.0,
      "end_time": 526540.0,
      "text": "for thousands of years."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 526540.0,
      "end_time": 529210.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re still right in the middle of the modern revolution--"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 529210.0,
      "end_time": 530660.0,
      "text": "maybe only at the beginning."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 530660.0,
      "end_time": 533240.0,
      "text": "The huge shift in human activity and a rise"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 533240.0,
      "end_time": 535090.0,
      "text": "in complexity may continue"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 535090.0,
      "end_time": 537540.0,
      "text": "long after our grandchildren&#39;s lifetimes."
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 537540.0,
      "end_time": 539630.0,
      "text": "That is, so long as we don&#39;t do something stupid,"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 539630.0,
      "end_time": 541270.0,
      "text": "which, you know, withhomo sapiens,"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 541270.0,
      "end_time": 542570.0,
      "text": "is always a distinct possibility."
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 542570.0,
      "end_time": 544240.0,
      "text": "And let&#39;s not forget about the rise in complexity"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 544240.0,
      "end_time": 545630.0,
      "text": "that&#39;s been happening since the beginning"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 545630.0,
      "end_time": 548300.0,
      "text": "of the universe 13.8 billion years ago."
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 548300.0,
      "end_time": 550840.0,
      "text": "A star is essentially a pile of hydrogen and helium."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 550840.0,
      "end_time": 552480.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s extremely simple."
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 552480.0,
      "end_time": 555780.0,
      "text": "By comparison, a brain that arose via biological evolution"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 555780.0,
      "end_time": 557630.0,
      "text": "is an intricate network of billions of connections"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 557630.0,
      "end_time": 559120.0,
      "text": "and building blocks."
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 559120.0,
      "end_time": 562030.0,
      "text": "Industrial society is an immense whirring global network"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 562030.0,
      "end_time": 564720.0,
      "text": "of millions upon millions of brains more closely connected"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 564720.0,
      "end_time": 566210.0,
      "text": "than ever before."
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 566210.0,
      "end_time": 569510.0,
      "text": "The products of this society raised complexity even further."
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 569510.0,
      "end_time": 572150.0,
      "text": "Bottom line is this, if the first part of this series,"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 572150.0,
      "end_time": 573720.0,
      "text": "which looked at the vastness of the universe,"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 573720.0,
      "end_time": 576720.0,
      "text": "made you feel insignificant, just remember that now"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 576720.0,
      "end_time": 579180.0,
      "text": "at the tremendous heights of technological progress,"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 579180.0,
      "end_time": 586210.0,
      "text": "humanity is, in terms of networks and building blocks:"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 586210.0,
      "end_time": 587750.0,
      "text": "And there&#39;s currently no end to the potential"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 587750.0,
      "end_time": 590120.0,
      "text": "for rising complexity in sight."
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 590120.0,
      "end_time": 591300.0,
      "text": "This brings us to a long-standing"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 591300.0,
      "end_time": 592780.0,
      "text": "historical question:"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 592780.0,
      "end_time": 595720.0,
      "text": "why did the Industrial Revolution happen in Britain?"
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 595720.0,
      "end_time": 598300.0,
      "text": "Great Britain was certainly uncommonly well positioned."
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 598300.0,
      "end_time": 600120.0,
      "text": "That said, so was China."
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 600120.0,
      "end_time": 601810.0,
      "text": "So why didn&#39;t the Industrial Revolution happen"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 601810.0,
      "end_time": 603810.0,
      "text": "in, say, Song Dynasty China"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 603810.0,
      "end_time": 606060.0,
      "text": "between the 10th and 13th centuries?"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 606060.0,
      "end_time": 610750.0,
      "text": "So, we know:"
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 610750.0,
      "end_time": 613150.0,
      "text": "And China has had both for a long time."
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 613150.0,
      "end_time": 615120.0,
      "text": "The medieval Chinese had much more advanced"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 615120.0,
      "end_time": 616630.0,
      "text": "agricultural methods than Europe."
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 616630.0,
      "end_time": 618720.0,
      "text": "They paid attention to weeding and growing crops"
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 618720.0,
      "end_time": 621720.0,
      "text": "in rows and frequently used tools like the seed drill."
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 621720.0,
      "end_time": 623180.0,
      "text": "And they were doing it all centuries"
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 623180.0,
      "end_time": 625330.0,
      "text": "before that stuff was even heard of in Europe."
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 625330.0,
      "end_time": 627300.0,
      "text": "In the 900s, the spread of wet rice farming"
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 627300.0,
      "end_time": 630240.0,
      "text": "in southern China raised the carrying capacity even further"
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 630240.0,
      "end_time": 633360.0,
      "text": "because rice fields simply produce more food."
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 633360.0,
      "end_time": 634570.0,
      "text": "They are more efficient."
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 634570.0,
      "end_time": 636450.0,
      "text": "Also, rice is easier to prepare"
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 636450.0,
      "end_time": 638450.0,
      "text": "than the laborious European process"
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 638450.0,
      "end_time": 640300.0,
      "text": "of turning wheat into bread."
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 640300.0,
      "end_time": 642000.0,
      "text": "So during the 10th and 11th centuries,"
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 642000.0,
      "end_time": 644720.0,
      "text": "the Chinese population increased from about 50 or 60 million"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 644720.0,
      "end_time": 646660.0,
      "text": "to about 120 million."
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 646660.0,
      "end_time": 649060.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s a lot of new innovators."
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 649060.0,
      "end_time": 651480.0,
      "text": "So many, in fact, that Song China came close"
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 651480.0,
      "end_time": 653570.0,
      "text": "to having a modern revolution of its own."
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 653570.0,
      "end_time": 656150.0,
      "text": "I mean, coal was used to manufacture iron."
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 656150.0,
      "end_time": 659030.0,
      "text": "Production increased from 19,000 metric tons per year"
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 659030.0,
      "end_time": 663600.0,
      "text": "around 900 CE to 113,000 metric tons by 1200 CE."
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 663600.0,
      "end_time": 666720.0,
      "text": "The Song Dynasty was the first to invent and harness the power"
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 666720.0,
      "end_time": 669240.0,
      "text": "of gunpowder, and then later in the 15th century,"
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 669240.0,
      "end_time": 672030.0,
      "text": "Zheng He conducted overseas explorations decades"
    },
    {
      "index": 273,
      "start_time": 672030.0,
      "end_time": 673330.0,
      "text": "before Columbus."
    },
    {
      "index": 274,
      "start_time": 673330.0,
      "end_time": 675300.0,
      "text": "Textile production showed the first ever signs"
    },
    {
      "index": 275,
      "start_time": 675300.0,
      "end_time": 678720.0,
      "text": "of mechanization in ways similar to the European spinning jenny."
    },
    {
      "index": 276,
      "start_time": 678720.0,
      "end_time": 681480.0,
      "text": "But China had dry coal while the British"
    },
    {
      "index": 277,
      "start_time": 681480.0,
      "end_time": 683750.0,
      "text": "needed to pump water out of their coal mines"
    },
    {
      "index": 278,
      "start_time": 683750.0,
      "end_time": 686030.0,
      "text": "in order to mine coal, which led the British"
    },
    {
      "index": 279,
      "start_time": 686030.0,
      "end_time": 687510.0,
      "text": "to build steam engines."
    },
    {
      "index": 280,
      "start_time": 687510.0,
      "end_time": 689270.0,
      "text": "So why didn&#39;t the modern revolution start"
    },
    {
      "index": 281,
      "start_time": 689270.0,
      "end_time": 691120.0,
      "text": "in China around 1000 CE?"
    },
    {
      "index": 282,
      "start_time": 691120.0,
      "end_time": 693690.0,
      "text": "Well, it might have been the cultural and political climate"
    },
    {
      "index": 283,
      "start_time": 693690.0,
      "end_time": 696210.0,
      "text": "and the shift away from innovation and commerce"
    },
    {
      "index": 284,
      "start_time": 696210.0,
      "end_time": 698660.0,
      "text": "at the end of Song China in 1279."
    },
    {
      "index": 285,
      "start_time": 698660.0,
      "end_time": 701630.0,
      "text": "Possibly because they hadn&#39;t united the world zones"
    },
    {
      "index": 286,
      "start_time": 701630.0,
      "end_time": 704510.0,
      "text": "in a network of trade and unified collective learning."
    },
    {
      "index": 287,
      "start_time": 704510.0,
      "end_time": 706360.0,
      "text": "And possibly because the right combination"
    },
    {
      "index": 288,
      "start_time": 706360.0,
      "end_time": 708000.0,
      "text": "of cultural innovations required"
    },
    {
      "index": 289,
      "start_time": 708000.0,
      "end_time": 710150.0,
      "text": "to launch a Cambrian-style explosion"
    },
    {
      "index": 290,
      "start_time": 710150.0,
      "end_time": 711600.0,
      "text": "of growth just didn&#39;t happen."
    },
    {
      "index": 291,
      "start_time": 711600.0,
      "end_time": 713000.0,
      "text": "The point is that collective learning"
    },
    {
      "index": 292,
      "start_time": 713000.0,
      "end_time": 714780.0,
      "text": "is such a powerful force that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 293,
      "start_time": 714780.0,
      "end_time": 717240.0,
      "text": "from the explosion of the world population"
    },
    {
      "index": 294,
      "start_time": 717240.0,
      "end_time": 719750.0,
      "text": "from only six million people 10,000 years ago"
    },
    {
      "index": 295,
      "start_time": 719750.0,
      "end_time": 723150.0,
      "text": "to the 954 million by the end of the Agrarian Era,"
    },
    {
      "index": 296,
      "start_time": 723150.0,
      "end_time": 725270.0,
      "text": "the right combination of ideas that lead"
    },
    {
      "index": 297,
      "start_time": 725270.0,
      "end_time": 726570.0,
      "text": "to the industrial explosion"
    },
    {
      "index": 298,
      "start_time": 726570.0,
      "end_time": 728060.0,
      "text": "might have happened almost anywhere."
    },
    {
      "index": 299,
      "start_time": 728060.0,
      "end_time": 731210.0,
      "text": "So long as there are brains to think and exchange ideas,"
    },
    {
      "index": 300,
      "start_time": 731210.0,
      "end_time": 737540.0,
      "text": "so long as there are energy flows on the earth..."
    },
    {
      "index": 301,
      "start_time": 737540.0,
      "end_time": 738660.0,
      "text": "The modern revolution was accompanied"
    },
    {
      "index": 302,
      "start_time": 738660.0,
      "end_time": 741090.0,
      "text": "by explosive growth in human population."
    },
    {
      "index": 303,
      "start_time": 741090.0,
      "end_time": 744090.0,
      "text": "It took 250,000 years for humanity"
    },
    {
      "index": 304,
      "start_time": 744090.0,
      "end_time": 745480.0,
      "text": "to achieve its first billion people."
    },
    {
      "index": 305,
      "start_time": 745480.0,
      "end_time": 749330.0,
      "text": "By 1900, the world&#39;s population was 1.6 billion."
    },
    {
      "index": 306,
      "start_time": 749330.0,
      "end_time": 752330.0,
      "text": "Today there are over 7 billion potential innovators"
    },
    {
      "index": 307,
      "start_time": 752330.0,
      "end_time": 754810.0,
      "text": "who are now connected by the lightning speed of the internet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 308,
      "start_time": 754810.0,
      "end_time": 757570.0,
      "text": "and collective learning is more powerful than ever."
    },
    {
      "index": 309,
      "start_time": 757570.0,
      "end_time": 759780.0,
      "text": "Humans now have unprecedented control"
    },
    {
      "index": 310,
      "start_time": 759780.0,
      "end_time": 761750.0,
      "text": "and power over the Earth&#39;s biosphere"
    },
    {
      "index": 311,
      "start_time": 761750.0,
      "end_time": 764330.0,
      "text": "which has prompted some scientists and scholars"
    },
    {
      "index": 312,
      "start_time": 764330.0,
      "end_time": 766660.0,
      "text": "to claim that the Holocene is over"
    },
    {
      "index": 313,
      "start_time": 766660.0,
      "end_time": 769240.0,
      "text": "and we now stand on the threshold of a new era,"
    },
    {
      "index": 314,
      "start_time": 769240.0,
      "end_time": 771090.0,
      "text": "the Anthropocene."
    },
    {
      "index": 315,
      "start_time": 771090.0,
      "end_time": 773360.0,
      "text": "During this age, we may continue to raise complexity"
    },
    {
      "index": 316,
      "start_time": 773360.0,
      "end_time": 776090.0,
      "text": "in our little pocket of the universe to wondrous new levels,"
    },
    {
      "index": 317,
      "start_time": 776090.0,
      "end_time": 779090.0,
      "text": "hopefully to the growing benefit of all humans"
    },
    {
      "index": 318,
      "start_time": 779090.0,
      "end_time": 780840.0,
      "text": "rather than just a privileged few."
    },
    {
      "index": 319,
      "start_time": 780840.0,
      "end_time": 783870.0,
      "text": "Thanks to collective learning, our potential is awesome."
    },
    {
      "index": 320,
      "start_time": 783870.0,
      "end_time": 785750.0,
      "text": "Unless, that is, we hit a wall,"
    },
    {
      "index": 321,
      "start_time": 785750.0,
      "end_time": 788120.0,
      "text": "like agrarian societies did every few centuries"
    },
    {
      "index": 322,
      "start_time": 788120.0,
      "end_time": 790600.0,
      "text": "when their population growth outstripped their rates"
    },
    {
      "index": 323,
      "start_time": 790600.0,
      "end_time": 792180.0,
      "text": "of agricultural innovation."
    },
    {
      "index": 324,
      "start_time": 792180.0,
      "end_time": 795540.0,
      "text": "We are now in an era of immense danger"
    },
    {
      "index": 325,
      "start_time": 795540.0,
      "end_time": 797270.0,
      "text": "where the modern global system of humanity"
    },
    {
      "index": 326,
      "start_time": 797270.0,
      "end_time": 800030.0,
      "text": "might exhaust the resources of the earth"
    },
    {
      "index": 327,
      "start_time": 800030.0,
      "end_time": 801630.0,
      "text": "in the same way that agricultural societies"
    },
    {
      "index": 328,
      "start_time": 801630.0,
      "end_time": 804150.0,
      "text": "often exhausted the resources of the field."
    },
    {
      "index": 329,
      "start_time": 804150.0,
      "end_time": 814150.0,
      "text": "More on that next time."
    }
  ]
}